#. Tag: para
#: suse_logfiles.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are several system services (<emphasis>daemons</emphasis>) that, along "
"with the kernel itself, regularly record the system status and specific "
"events onto log files. This way, the administrator can regularly check the "
"status of the system at a certain point in time, recognize errors or faulty "
"functions and troubleshoot them with pinpoint precision. These log files are "
"normally stored in <filename>/var/log</filename> as specified by FHS and "
"grow on a daily basis. The <systemitem>logrotate</systemitem> package helps "
"control the growth of these files."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: suse_logfiles.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure logrotate with the file <indexterm> <primary>configuration files</"
"primary> <secondary>logrotate.conf</secondary> </indexterm> <filename>/etc/"
"logrotate.conf</filename>. In particular, the <systemitem>include</"
"systemitem> specification primarily configures the additional files to read. "
"Programs that produce log files install individual configuration files in "
"<filename>/etc/logrotate.d</filename>. For example, such files ship with the "
"packages <systemitem>apache2</systemitem> (<filename>/etc/logrotate.d/"
"apache2</filename>) and <systemitem>syslog-service</systemitem> (<filename>/"
"etc/logrotate.d/syslog</filename>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: suse_logfiles.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example for /etc/logrotate.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: suse_logfiles.xml:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# see \"man logrotate\" for details\n"
"# rotate log files weekly\n"
"weekly\n"
"\n"
"# keep 4 weeks worth of backlogs\n"
"rotate 4\n"
"\n"
"# create new (empty) log files after rotating old ones\n"
"create\n"
"\n"
"# uncomment this if you want your log files compressed\n"
"#compress\n"
"\n"
"# RPM packages drop log rotation information into this directory\n"
"include /etc/logrotate.d\n"
"\n"
"# no packages own lastlog or wtmp - we'll rotate them here\n"
"#/var/log/wtmp {\n"
"#    monthly\n"
"#    create 0664 root utmp\n"
"#    rotate 1\n"
"#}\n"
"\n"
"# system-specific logs may be also be configured here."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: suse_logfiles.xml:46
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"logrotate is controlled through cron and is called daily by <filename>/etc/"
"cron.daily/logrotate</filename>."
msgstr ""

